Timezones: A webapp for managing timezones.

This web application is composed of two, clearly separated, applications.

One of them runs in the server and acts as a RESTful api server.
The other one, it runs on the browser and acts as a client for the above mentioned api.

JSON Web Tokens are being used for authentification.

The following is a list of libraries/frameworks being used in this project:

Sass (http://sass-lang.com)
Node.js (http://nodejs.org)
Sqlite (http://www.sqlite.org)
Express.js (http://expressjs.com)
Angular.js (http://angularjs.org)
Sequelize.js (http://sequelizejs.com)
jQuery (http://jquery.com)
jsonwebtoken (https://github.com/auth0/node-jsonwebtoken)
Gulp.js (http://gulpjs.com)
Moment.js (http://momentjs.com)
